  "genie_instructions": "ALWAYS prefer metric views with MEASURE() syntax for aggregation questions. The turbine_kpi_monthly view (source: wind_turbines) has dimensions: record_date, turbine_model, wind_farm, turbine_status. Measures: total_generation_mwh, avg_capacity_factor, avg_wind_speed, generating_count, total_turbine_count. The wind_forecast_monthly view (source: wind_snapshots) has dimensions: snapshot_date, wind_farm. Measures: total_forecasted_mwh, total_actual_mwh, total_curtailment_mwh, total_revenue, avg_availability. Use GROUP BY ALL with MEASURE() queries. Only query base tables directly when the question requires columns not available as metric view dimensions (e.g. turbine_id, turbine_name).",
  "sample_questions": [
    "What is the monthly trend in generating count?",
    "How has unique total turbines changed over time?",
    "What is the monthly trend in highest generation mwh?",
    "How has total wind generation mwh changed over time?",
    "What is the monthly trend in unique turbines?",
    "How has highest forecasted generation mwh changed over time?",
    "What is the monthly trend in total forecasted generation mwh?"
